# Rule 030 - Mode Policy

## Default stance

Start new tasks in **Plan mode** (Cursor Plan mode OR Claude Code `plan` mode). Only drop to lower-supervision modes after a checkpoint was taken.

## Decision matrix

| Situation | Surface | Mode | Model |
|---|---|---|---|
| Explore unfamiliar area | Cursor Ask | ask | Sonnet 4.6 or Auto |
| Multi-file change | Cursor Plan -> Claude CLI | plan | Sonnet 4.6 |
| Single-line fix | Cursor Agent | default | Auto |
| Rename / migration | Claude CLI | plan | Opus 4.6 |
| UI polish | Cursor Agent | default | Composer 2 |
| Debug an error | Claude CLI | default, then plan if scope grows | Sonnet 4.6 |
| Long autonomous run | Claude CLI in worktree | plan, then auto | Sonnet 4.6 |
| Generate tests | Claude CLI | plan | Sonnet 4.6 |
| Sensitive refactor | Claude CLI after checkpoint | acceptEdits | Opus 4.6 |
| PR review | Claude CLI | default | Sonnet 4.6 |

## Forbidden

- `bypassPermissions` outside a sandbox with no internet.
- `auto` mode on the main working tree.
- Running Cursor Agent and Claude Code on the same file simultaneously.

## Checkpoints

Take a checkpoint before:

- any `/execute` run
- dropping from `plan` to `acceptEdits` or `auto`
- any rename / migration

Name the checkpoint with the phase and task id.
